# Generated by: Claude Sonnet 4.6
#
# Read-only inspection tool for ~/.config/wayland-desktop/config.yaml.
# Supports listing all properties and looking up individual values by
# dot-separated path.
#
# COMMANDS
# --------
#   list
#       Print all top-level keys and their values.  Dict values are shown as
#       indented sub-keys.  Long lists (e.g. system_classes) are summarised.
#
#   lookup <key>
#       Return the value at <key>.  Dot notation navigates into nested dicts:
#
#           lookup progress_window          → true
#           lookup apps.brave.single_instance → false
#           lookup screens.main             → HDMI-A-2
#           lookup maximize.height_tolerance → 50
#
#       Output is printed with no trailing newline, suitable for shell capture:
#           FOLDER=$(getconfig lookup user_scripts_folder)
#
#       Exits 0 on success, 1 if the key path is not found.
#
# USAGE
# -----
#   python3 wayland/kwin_getconfig.py list
#   python3 wayland/kwin_getconfig.py lookup progress_window
#   python3 wayland/kwin_getconfig.py lookup apps.brave.single_instance
#
#   # Via the getconfig wrapper (from the project root):
#   getconfig list
#   getconfig lookup user_scripts_folder
#   FOLDER=$(getconfig lookup user_scripts_folder)
#
# CONFIG FILE RESOLUTION
# ----------------------
#   Uses the same search order as kwin_restore.py:
#   1. --config FILE (explicit path, ~ expanded)
#   2. ~/.config/wayland-desktop/config.yaml (default)
#
# OPTIONS
#   --config FILE   Alternate config file path (~ is expanded)
